Scores of people are feared dead while many trapped under rubble after a building collapsed in Abraka, Ethiope East Council Area, Delta State. The building is a yet-to-be completed structure meant for a hotel which is located along Aghwana Avenue. Although the causalities are uncertain but eyewitnesses say the incident occurred on Saturday morning following a heavy downpour. According to the eyewitness four workers who had arrived early for the dayâ€™s job were trapped and feared dead. However rescue efforts are still ongoing at the scene of the incident. Source: Channels TV